===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|uncountable}} an attitude of consideration or high [[regard#Noun|regard]]
#: {{ux|en|He is an intellectual giant, and I have great '''respect''' for him.}}
#: {{ux|en|We do respect people for their dignity and worth.}}
#: {{syn|en|deference|esteem|consideration|regard|fealty|reverence|aught}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} good opinion, honor, or admiration
#: {{syn|en|admiration|esteem|reverence|regard|recognition|veneration|honor}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable|always plural}} Polite [[greetings]], often offered as [[condolences]] after a death.
#: {{ux|en|The mourners paid their last '''respects''' to the deceased poet.}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} a particular [[aspect]], [[feature]] or [[detail]] of something
#* '''1609''', {{w|William Shakespeare}}, Sonnet 36:
#*: In our two loves there is but one '''respect'''
#: {{ux|en|This year's model is superior to last year's in several '''respects'''.}}
#: {{syn|en|aspect|dimension|face|facet|side}}
# Good will; favor
#* '''1611''', {{w|King James Version}}, Exodus 2:25:
#*: And God looked upon the children of Israel, and God had '''respect''' unto them.

